Real Goods - Wikipedia






















 






Real Goods

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Real Goods





Type

Corporation


Genre
Off-grid and sustainable living


Founded
1978


Founder
John Schaeffer


Headquarters
13771 S. Highway 101, Hopland, California, USA



Key people

President and Founder
John Schaeffer


Products
Renewable energy systems, homesteading, sustainable living goods


Website
RealGoods.com


Real Goods Trading Corporation (commonly referred to as Real Goods) is a retail store and mail order / e-commerce business located in Hopland, California that sells renewable energy systems, homesteading supplies, and other environmentally friendly goods and resources for people interested in living off the grid or with a low environmental impact.



Contents


1 History of Real Goods

1.1 Origin of Real Goods
1.2 Partnership with Gaiam and the Birth of Real Goods Solar
1.3 Initial Public Offering and Solar Installation Expansion
1.4 A Return to the Real Goods Roots


2 Solar Living Center

