RGS Energy Management Team


Get to know the leaders of our clean energy company









Dennis Lacey, Chief Executive Officer
Dennis Lacey came to RGS Energy with over 25 years of executive leadership experience. Prior to RGS Energy, he served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at Imperial Bancorp, a $6 billion publicly traded commercial bank. Before Imperial Bancorp, Dennis was president and Chief Executive Officer of Capital Associates, a publicly traded equipment leasing company. His experience also includes serving as Chief Financial Officer for CKE Restaurants and TeleTech, one of the largest customer experience management companies in the United
States, and as head of capital markets for a private alternative asset investment and management firm.
 
 
Seth Wiggins, Vice President of Sales
Seth Wiggins built RGS Energy’s call center which consists of two departments, lead generation and inside sales. Prior to RGS Energy, he served as Director of Sales at Syndicated Solar (acquired by RGS Energy). Before Syndicated Solar he served as President of Millennium Development Corporation, a property development, general construction, and commercial solar construction company which developed projects ranging from $1-20 million. Seth has held several General and Civil Contractor’s Licenses and is accredited by the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP™ Certified Solar Installer)
 
 
Alan Fine, Vice President of Operations and Principal Financial Officer
Alan Fine previously serves as Treasurer and Principal Financial Officer at RGS Energy, in addition to Vice President of Operations at Sunetric. He previously served as the Chief Financial Officer and Principal Accounting Officer for several public and private companies, including
Roomlinx, Pearlstine Distributors, Colorado Greenhouse, and Gold Coast Beverage Distributors. Alan’s prior experience includes 7+ years as a licensed professional engineer (PE in civil) in Maryland and Delaware, engineering residential land development projects totaling 8,000 home
sites.
 
 

Karen Rainone, Human Resources Director
Karen Rainone joined RGS Energy in 2013 and has more than 10 years of diverse human resources and management experience that includes start-ups and established organizations. She has extensive hands-on experience leading HR initiatives including policy design, compensation, performance management, recruiting, HRIS implementations, training, development, and benefits administration. Prior to joining RGS Energy, Karen served as Human Resources Manager at Roomlinx, as well as Payroll and Benefits Manager at Clinica Family Health Services.
 
 







 




